  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Anathoth with her suburbs,.... This is not mentioned among the cities of Benjamin, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 18:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; it was the native place of the Prophet Jeremiah; see Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 1:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; it lay about two or three miles north of Jerusalem; three, says, Jerom (k). Rauwolff (l) speaks of it as a small village, when he travelled into those parts, and as lying on a height or eminence, and which was within twenty furlongs of Jerusalem, as Josephus writes (m): ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Almon with her suburbs; this also is not mentioned among the cities of Benjamin, Joshua 18:11; it is called Alemeth, 1 Chronicles 6:60. Jarchi and Kimchi say it is the same with Bahurim, 2 Samuel 3:16; where the Targum renders it by Almeth, and both words signify the same thing, \"youth\": ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and Almon with her suburbs; this also is not mentioned among the cities of Benjamin, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 18:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; it is called Alemeth, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 6:60",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Jarchi and Kimchi say it is the same with Bahurim, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 3:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; where the Targum renders it by Almeth, and both words signify the same thing, \"youth\": ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "four cities; which were a large number for so small a tribe as little Benjamin to give. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(k) De loc. Heb. fol. 88. H. (l) Travels, par. 3. c. 2. p. 216. (m) Antiqu. l. 10. c. 7. sect. 3.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(k) De loc. Heb. fol. 88. H. (l) Travels, par. 3. c. 2. p. 216. (m) Antiqu. l. 10. c. 7. sect. 3.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
